news.title: Kolkata: Licensed surveyors can now sanction building plans on land up to three cottahs
news.para: ​Under a new rule, the citizens having a small chunk of land — measuring up to 3 cottahs — can rope in an architect or an LBS and apply for a building sanction online to bypass unnecessary delays in getting the construction permit from the Kolkata Municipal Corporation.

news.title: GDA board clears master plan 2031, Ghaziabad set to get seven 'influence zones'
news.para: The three individual plans for Ghaziabad, Loni and Modinagar/Muradnagar were approved as one unified master plan for the entire Ghaziabad district.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body demolishes illegal colony in Giaspura
news.para: Assistant town planner (ATP - Zone C) Pardeep Sehgal and building inspector Paulparneet Singh said that on the directions of MC commissioner Sandeep Rishi, regular drives were being conducted to prevent illegal constructions in the city.

news.title: Panvel civic body allows property tax exemption for ex-servicemen
news.para: The waiver has been implemented in retrospective effect from April 1, 2023. According to PCMC, 55% of the total property tax is being collected under the head of general tax from the property holders.

news.title: Hyderabad: I-T seizes Rs 2 crore from King's Group of Companies
news.para: King's Group is a family business founded by Shanawaz, while Mohammed Zubairuddin, Mohammed Naseeruddin and Shaifuddin are directors. While I-T sleuths are investigating into Shanawaz's political links, he denied having any.

news.title: BMRCL set to start landwork for Bengaluru metro phase-III
news.para: ​In the first stage, 100 acres of land has been identified for building a depot and viaducts on some of the stretches of the corridor. A joint survey of the properties identified for acquisition is expected to start shortly, according to officials.

news.title: Gujarat SCDRC orders Sambhav Infrastructure to give possession of flats
news.para: The case involved five consumers, Naresh Balwani from Gandhidham, Mehulbharthi Goswami, Heena Khorasiya, Chakshu Suthar and Lalit Soni.

news.title: Bengaluru: Slum clearance sparks property tax surge proposal
news.para: ​The commission’s report, submitted to Chief Minister Siddaramaiah, proposed various measures, including the clearance of slums, which could necessitate increased contributions from taxpayers.

news.title: ED arrests woman in money-laundering case against Lucknow's Shine group
news.para: A special court dealing with cases lodged under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) has sent the accused to the ED's custody till November 30, it said.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Land survey done, loop to link DME with Crossings Republik gets nod
news.para: A survey undertaken to measure the rate of traffic flow on the speedway showed around 40,000 passenger car units (PCU) use the NH9 per day and 10,000 PCUs use the DME.

news.title: SEBI to oversee online platforms offering fraction real estate assets
news.para: In a statement after its quarterly board meeting, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) also said that fresh investments by alternative investment funds would be stored electronically from Sept. 2024.

news.title: Gurugram: HSVP issues notices to residents seeking Rs 409 crore in a month
news.para: The residents have been asked to pay up Rs 30 lakh to Rs 1 crore depending upon the size of their plots within 30 days or face penalties in the form of interest on the recovery amount.

news.title: Sebi to amend REIT, AIF norms; proposes regulatory framework for index providers
news.para: Briefing reporters after the meeting, Sebi Chairperson Madhabi Puri Buch said the objective of the Small and Medium Real Estate Investment Trusts (SM REITs) is to help expand the market significantly so that more retail investors can have fractional ownership in REIT units.

news.title: FIR filed against Emaar Properties on MGF's complaint after court order in Gurugram: Police
news.para: Following an order by Chief Judicial Magistrate Ramesh Chander on November 18, the FIR was registered on November 20 against EMAAR Properties PJSC and its Indian subsidiary, Emaar India Ltd, its director Bharat Bhushan Garg and others, the police said.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body serves notices to 100 commercial properties
news.para: Now, all such defaulters have fifteen days to pay their dues, failing which they will not be given any notices or information and their properties will be sealed.

news.title: ED searches DLF in money laundering case against Supertech
news.para: DLF, later in a stock market filing, said "a team of officials from the Enforcement Directorate visited our premises seeking information with respect to investigation being conducted in the matter of Supertech."

news.title: NGPDA adopts land use map of Panaji
news.para: The land use map and register were accepted by the town and country planning board on November 10 after making some modifications in the land use register.

news.title: Over 55 lakh people have received houses in last six years: Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: The chief minister made the remarks while inaugurating and laying the foundation stone of 116 development works worth Rs 175 crore at Yogiraj Baba Gambhirnath Auditorium in Gorakhpur, the UP government said in a statement.

news.title: How cut in registration fees will cost home-buyers more in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Home-buyers and developers had hitherto been registering a sale deed of undivided share (UDS) of the land and a construction agreement for the built-up area in case of flats/apartments.

news.title: Pune metro stretch to Ramwadi up for launch in December 2023
news.para: The Maha Metro has started speed trials of rakes till Ramwadi, for which technical teams are checking the alignment of tracks, curves, elevation and other technical parameters, such as signalling and telecommunication.
